/Huxisanxiaotu.jpg/210px-Huxisanxiaotu.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/74/Huxisanxiaotu.jpg/280px-Huxisanxiaotu.jpg 2x" data-file-width="724" data-file-height="400" /></a></div>\n</div>\n<div class="gallerytext">\n<p><i>Confucianism, Taoism, and Buddhism are one</i>, a painting in the Litang style, 12th century.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 175px">\n<div style="width: 175px">\n<div class="thumb" style="width: 170px;">\n<div style="margin:15px auto;"><a href="/wiki/File:Huang_Zhucai,_Mountain_Magpie,_Sparrows_and_Bramble.jpg" class="image"><img alt="a portrait oriented painting with a large white bird with a black head in the foreground, and several smaller birds perched on a cluster of small branches and fern in the background." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Huang_Zhucai%2C_Mountain_Magpie%2C_Sparrows_and_Bramble.jpg/76px-Huang_Zhucai%2C_Mountain_Magpie%2C_Sparrows_and_Bramble.jpg" width="76" height="140" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Huang_Zhucai%2C_Mountain_Magpie%2C_Sparrows_and_Bramble.jpg/115px-Huang_Zhucai%2C_Mountain_Magpie%2C_Sparrows_and_Bramble.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Huang_Zhucai%2C_Mountain_Magpie%2C_Sparrows_and_Bramble.jpg/153px-Huang_Zhucai%2C_Mountain_Magpie%2C_Sparrows_and_Bramble.jpg 2x" data-file-width="301" data-file-height="550" /></a></div>\n</div>\n<div class="gallerytext">\n<p><i>Mountain Magpie, Sparrows and Bramble</i>, by Huang Zhucai (933\xe2\x80\x93after 993).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 175px">\n<div style="width: 175px">\n<div class="thumb" style="width: 170px;">\n<div style="margin:15px auto;"><a href="/wiki/File:B_Song_Dynasty_Cao_Empress_Sitting_with_Maids.JPG" class="image"><img alt="A square painting of a woman in an intricately decorated blue dress and a large blue hat, sitting in a throne. She is flanked by two female attendants in black