ikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Song_celadon_5-tube_jar_and_cover.JPG/105px-Song_celadon_5-tube_jar_and_cover.JPG" width="105" height="140" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Song_celadon_5-tube_jar_and_cover.JPG/157px-Song_celadon_5-tube_jar_and_cover.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/14/Song_celadon_5-tube_jar_and_cover.JPG/210px-Song_celadon_5-tube_jar_and_cover.JPG 2x" data-file-width="1704" data-file-height="2272" /></a></div>\n</div>\n<div class="gallerytext">\n<p>A Song five-tubed jar with lotus petal design, made of <a href="/wiki/Longquan_celadon" title="Longquan celadon">Longquan celadon</a></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 175px">\n<div style="width: 175px">\n<div class="thumb" style="width: 170px;">\n<div style="margin:32.5px auto;"><a href="/wiki/File:Stoneware_tea_bowls,_Song_Dynasty.jpg" class="image"><img alt="Two small polished black bowls. One has a large blue streak in it, the other has a polka-dot pattern on the inside consisting of black spots on a dark grey background. All of the coloring is created by features of the stone, rather than paint." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Stoneware_tea_bowls%2C_Song_Dynasty.jpg/140px-Stoneware_tea_bowls%2C_Song_Dynasty.jpg" width="140" height="105" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Stoneware_tea_bowls%2C_Song_Dynasty.jpg/210px-Stoneware_tea_bowls%2C_Song_Dynasty.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Stoneware_tea_bowls%2C_Song_Dynasty.jpg/280px-Stoneware_tea_bowls%2C_Song_Dynasty.jpg 2x" data-file-width="3072" data-file-height="2304" /></a></div>\n</div>\n<div class="gallerytext">\n<p>A pair of <a href="/wiki/Stoneware" title="Stoneware">stoneware</a> tea bowls from the Song</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</center>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Sculpture">Sculpture</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket